0) Requisitos

En WSL Ubuntu:

sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y qemu-kvm libvirt-daemon-system libvirt-clients dnsmasq-base virt-manager

Instalar plugin de Vagrant para libvirt:

vagrant plugin install vagrant-libvirt

Añadir usuario a los grupos necesarios:

sudo usermod -aG libvirt,kvm $USER
newgrp libvirt

Activar libvirt:

sudo systemctl enable --now libvirtd

1) Crear carpeta del laboratorio

mkdir -p ~/iac-lab
cd ~/iac-lab

2) Añadir la box

vagrant box add generic/ubuntu2204 --provider=libvirt

3) Crear el Vagrantfile

nano Vagrantfile
Vagrant.configure("2") do |config|
  config.vm.box = "generic/ubuntu2204"

  LAB_NET = "192.168.56"

  # VM WEB
  config.vm.define "vm2" do |vm|
    vm.vm.hostname = "web"
    vm.vm.network "private_network", ip: "#{LAB_NET}.12"

    vm.vm.provider :libvirt do |libvirt|
      libvirt.memory = 1024
      libvirt.cpus = 1
    end

    vm.vm.provision "shell", inline: <<-SHELL
      sudo apt update
      sudo apt install -y nginx

      echo "<h1>Servidor WEB funcionando</h1>" | sudo tee /var/www/html/index.html

      sudo systemctl enable nginx
      sudo systemctl restart nginx
    SHELL
  end


  # VM PROXY
  config.vm.define "vm1" do |vm|
    vm.vm.hostname = "proxy"
    vm.vm.network "private_network", ip: "#{LAB_NET}.11"

    # abrir puerto hacia tu PC
    vm.vm.network "forwarded_port", guest: 8443, host: 8443

    vm.vm.provider :libvirt do |libvirt|
      libvirt.memory = 1024
      libvirt.cpus = 1
    end

    vm.vm.provision "shell", inline: <<-SHELL
      sudo apt update
      sudo apt install -y nginx

      sudo rm -f /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/default

      sudo tee /etc/nginx/conf.d/proxy.conf <<EOF
server {
    listen 8443;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://192.168.56.12;
    }
}
EOF

      sudo systemctl enable nginx
      sudo systemctl restart nginx
    SHELL
  end

end

4) Arrancar las máquinas

cd ~/iac-lab
export VAGRANT_DEFAULT_PROVIDER=libvirt
vagrant up --no-parallel

5) Acceder al servicio

Abrir en el navegador:
